  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 425°F (220°C).",
    "In a large mixing bowl, combine cheddar cheese, olive oil, smoked paprika, salt, and pepper. Mix well.",
    "Add broccoli florets, red bell pepper slices, onion, and garlic cloves into the bowl with cheese mixture. Toss to coat evenly.",
    "Transfer the mixture onto a baking sheet lined with parchment paper. Arrange in an even layer and bake for 20 minutes.",
    "Gently stir the mixture and add low-sodium broth back into the baking dish. Bake for another 10 minutes until all vegetables are tender and cheese is fully melted and bubbly.",
    "Remove from oven and let cool slightly before serving."
  ],
